Description: CVE-2026-47166 - Fix heap buffer over-read and improper authentication
 in distributed pixel cache server. The server fails to validate recv() return
 length when reading session keys, causing a heap buffer over-read. Additionally,
 the authentication uses predictable GetMagickSignature() rather than proper HMAC,
 allowing unauthorized access. This patch introduces SipHash-2-4 based HMAC
 challenge-response authentication and fixes the recv() length validation.
Origin: upstream, commit:d3b02f25be7d2e097c4e0af90fe2535954381063
Author: Cristy <urban-warrior@imagemagick.org>
Last-Update: 2026-05-25

